I don't know what's the idea behind

`img, embed, iframe, object, video {
    height: auto;
    max-width: 100%;
}`

but it´s not working for me. And I can't even overwrite it, there is no option for "height" that can undo this. So I can not use Bulma at the moment whatsoever.

### Overview of the problem

This is about the Bulma **CSS framework** 
<!-- This is about the Bulma **Docs** -->
I'm using Bulma **version** [0.7.5]
<!-- My **browser** is: -->
This is a **Sass** issue: I'm using version [4.12.0]
<!-- I am sure this issue is **not a duplicate**? -->

### Description

Using a color from `findColorInvert` to `$primary-invert` make the compiler crash.

### Steps to Reproduce

```sass
@import "../node_modules/bulma/sass/utilities/initial-variables";
$pink: #ffcfd1;
$pink-invert: rgba(0,0,0,0.7);
$pink-invert: findColorInvert($pink);
$primary: $pink;
$primary-invert: $pink-invert;
@import "../node_modules/bulma/bulma";
```

### Expected behavior

Compiled css.

### Actual behavior

```
> node-sass _sass/main.scss build/main.css

{
  "status": 1,
  "file": "/app/node_modules/bulma/sass/elements/button.sass",
  "line": 150,
  "column": 29,
  "message": "argument `$color` of `darken($color, $amount)` must be a color",
  "formatted": "Error: argument `$color` of `darken($color, $amount)` must be a color\n        on line 150 of node_modules/bulma/sass/elements/button.sass, in function `darken`\n        from line 150 of node_modules/bulma/sass/elements/button.sass\n        from line 4 of node_modules/bulma/sass/elements/_all.sass\n        from line 5 of node_modules/bulma/bulma.sass\n        from line 19 of _sass/main.scss\n>>           background-color: darken($color-invert, 5%); }\n\n   ----------------------------^\n"
}
